{
  "texts": [
    "It has been argued that most current DL algorithms are not suitable for applications in tasks where comparisons with previous images are necessary 74.",
    "Developing DL algorithms that can process longitudinal imaging data, therefore, plays an important role towards advancing DL in radiology.",
    "Kickingereder et al.",
    "developed an application-ready software infrastructure for deep-learning-based segmentation of brain tumors 16.",
    "They utilized spatial and temporal tumor volume dynamics to predict patient time to progression."
  ]
}